President Obama will host President Xi Jinping of China for an official State Visit at the White House on September 25, 2015. This visit aims to strengthen cooperation between the United States and China on various global, regional, and bilateral issues. The visit will also allow President Obama and President Xi to address areas of disagreement in a constructive manner. A State Dinner will be held in honor of President Xi and Madame Peng Liyuan on the evening of September 25.